17. Reference Commands by Use Case
This section groups the most important Nmap options by what they are used for.
Use case	Common command	Why it matters
Host discovery	-sn, -Pn	Controls whether you only find live hosts or assume they are live.
TCP discovery	-sS, -sT	Chooses between SYN scanning and full TCP connect scanning.
UDP discovery	-sU	Checks services like DNS, SNMP, NTP, and DHCP.
Service detection	-sV, --version-light, --version-all	Shows what application is likely running on an open port.
OS detection	-O	Estimates the operating system or device family.
Scripts	-sC, --script, --script-args	Adds scripted checks for more detail.
Output	-oN, -oX, -oG, -oA	Saves results in the format you need.
Speed control	-T, --min-rate, --max-rate, --max-retries	Balances speed, reliability, and network load.
